The article discusses the issue of illegal immigration and the impact it has on the immigration system in the United States. It highlights the frustration with district courts issuing nationwide injunctions that force open borders policies onto the American people. Specifically, it mentions a district court in California that has halted the use of a federal law allowing for the return of illegal and inadmissible aliens to Mexico while they await asylum hearings. This decision is seen as undermining the President's ability to address the crisis at the border and disrupts the conduct of foreign affairs. The article concludes by stating that the Executive Branch intends to appeal and take necessary action to defend its efforts to resolve the crisis.